“There will be ever increasing wind and stormy weather will push northwards. There will be of heavy rain, torrential rain, particularly in the North East and places like Dartmoor.” Gusts of up to 60mph are expected, but these could increase to 80mph along coastal areas. The Met Office has issued a yellow weather warning for parts of England on Monday. The storms are set to continue throughout Christmas Eve, with rain continuing in the South East. But by Christmas Day the storm is expected to subside, with fewer showers and a chance of snow, particularly in Scotland. Mr Maccoll added: “There will be plenty of better weather on Christmas Day for people to get out and about and walk off all those Christmas dinners.”
Ladbrokes had been offering 12/1 for snow on Christmas Day in London as recently as Friday morning but those odds have been slashed to just 6/1 in little more than 24 hours. Weather
